#. <section class="sutta" id="mn152"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn152:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 152"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 152"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn152:0.2"
msgid "Indriyabhāvanāsutta"
msgstr "The Development of the Faculties"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.298"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "mn152:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

# Keep consistency with AN 10.28
#. </span>
#. VAR: gajaṅgalāyaṃ → kajaṅgalāyaṃ (bj, pts1) | kajjaṅgalāyaṃ (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: suveḷuvane → mukheluvane (bj, pts1) | sukheluvane (si) | veḷuvane (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn152:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gajaṅgalāyaṃ viharati suveḷuvane."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kajaṅgalā in a bamboo grove."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn152:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uttaro māṇavo pārāsiviyantevāsī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then the brahmin student Uttara, a pupil of the brahmin Pārāsariya, "
"approached the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "mn152:2.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnaṃ kho uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ pārāsiviyantevāsiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "mn152:2.3"
msgid "“deseti, uttara, pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Uttara, does Pārāsariya teach his disciples the development of the "
"faculties?”"

msgctxt "mn152:2.4"
msgid "“Deseti, bho gotama, pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanan”ti."
msgstr "“He does, Master Gotama.”"

msgctxt "mn152:2.5"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana, uttara, deseti pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ "
"indriyabhāvanan”ti?"
msgstr "“But how does he teach it?”"

msgctxt "mn152:2.6"
msgid "“Idha, bho gotama, cakkhunā rūpaṃ na passati, sotena saddaṃ na suṇāti—"
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, it’s when the eye sees no sight and the ear hears no sound."

msgctxt "mn152:2.7"
msgid ""
"evaṃ kho, bho gotama, deseti pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ "
"indriyabhāvanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how Pārāsariya teaches his disciples the development of the "
"faculties.”"

msgctxt "mn152:2.8"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ sante kho, uttara, andho bhāvitindriyo bhavissati, badhiro "
"bhāvitindriyo bhavissati;"
msgstr ""
"“In that case, Uttara, a blind person and a deaf person will have developed "
"faculties"

msgctxt "mn152:2.9"
msgid "yathā pārāsiviyassa brāhmaṇassa vacanaṃ."
msgstr "according to what Pārāsariya says."

msgctxt "mn152:2.10"
msgid ""
"Andho hi, uttara, cakkhunā rūpaṃ na passati, badhiro sotena saddaṃ na "
"suṇātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For a blind person sees no sight with the eye and a deaf person hears no "
"sound with the ear.”"

msgctxt "mn152:2.11"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, uttaro māṇavo pārāsiviyantevāsī tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto "
"pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When he said this, Uttara sat silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, "
"downcast, depressed, with nothing to say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.299"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn152:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ pārāsiviyantevāsiṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ maṅkubhūtaṃ "
"pattakkhandhaṃ adhomukhaṃ pajjhāyantaṃ appaṭibhānaṃ viditvā āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Knowing this, the Buddha addressed Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "mn152:3.2"
msgid ""
"“aññathā kho, ānanda, deseti pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanaṃ, "
"aññathā ca panānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, the development of the faculties taught by Pārāsariya is quite "
"different from the supreme development of the faculties in the training of "
"the noble one.”"

msgctxt "mn152:3.3"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One. "

msgctxt "mn152:3.4"
msgid ""
"yaṃ bhagavā ariyassa vinaye anuttaraṃ indriyabhāvanaṃ deseyya. Bhagavato "
"sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Let the Buddha teach the supreme development of the faculties in the "
"training of the noble one. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "mn152:3.5"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn152:3.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "mn152:3.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn152:4.1"
msgid "“Kathañcānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā hoti?"
msgstr ""
"“And how, Ānanda, is there the supreme development of the faculties in the "
"training of the noble one?"

msgctxt "mn152:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati "
"amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, liking, disliking, and both "
"liking and disliking come up in them."

msgctxt "mn152:4.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

msgctxt "mn152:4.4"
msgid ""
"‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ."
msgstr "‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me."

msgctxt "mn152:4.5"
msgid "Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ."
msgstr "That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated."

msgctxt "mn152:4.6"
msgid "Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "But this is peaceful and sublime, namely"

msgctxt "mn152:4.7"
msgid "upekkhā’ti."
msgstr "equanimity.’"

msgctxt "mn152:4.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ "
"nirujjhati;"
msgstr ""
"Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in "
"them cease,"

msgctxt "mn152:4.9"
msgid "upekkhā saṇṭhāti."
msgstr "and equanimity becomes stabilized."

msgctxt "mn152:4.10"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, cakkhumā puriso ummīletvā vā nimīleyya, nimīletvā vā "
"ummīleyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like how a person with good sight might open their eyes then shut them; "
"or might shut their eyes then open them."

msgctxt "mn152:4.11"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena "
"uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, "
"upekkhā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr ""
"Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, "
"and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and "
"equanimity becomes stabilized."

msgctxt "mn152:4.12"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā cakkhuviññeyyesu "
"rūpesu."
msgstr ""
"In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of "
"the faculties regarding sights known by the eye."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn152:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno sotena saddaṃ sutvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, "
"uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when a mendicant hears a sound with their ears, liking, "
"disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them."

msgctxt "mn152:5.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

msgctxt "mn152:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ."
msgstr "‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me."

msgctxt "mn152:5.4"
msgid "Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ."
msgstr "That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated."

