"them cease,"

msgctxt "mn152:7.8"
msgid "upekkhā saṇṭhāti."
msgstr "and equanimity becomes stabilized."

#. VAR: vameyya → vammeyya (s1-3) | sandhameyya (mr)
msgctxt "mn152:7.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso jivhagge kheḷapiṇḍaṃ saṃyūhitvā "
"appakasirena vameyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like how a strong person who’s formed a glob of spit on the tip of "
"their tongue could easily spit it out."

msgctxt "mn152:7.10"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena "
"uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, "
"upekkhā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr ""
"Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, "
"and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and "
"equanimity becomes stabilized."

msgctxt "mn152:7.11"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā jivhāviññeyyesu "
"rasesu."
msgstr ""
"In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of "
"the faculties regarding tastes known by the tongue."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn152:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā uppajjati "
"manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when a mendicant feels a touch with their body, liking, "
"disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them."

msgctxt "mn152:8.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

msgctxt "mn152:8.3"
msgid ""
