msgid "upekkhā’ti."
msgstr "equanimity.’"

msgctxt "mn152:8.7"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ "
"nirujjhati;"
msgstr ""
"Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in "
"them cease,"

msgctxt "mn152:8.8"
msgid "upekkhā saṇṭhāti."
msgstr "and equanimity becomes stabilized."

msgctxt "mn152:8.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ "
"vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;"
msgstr "It’s like how a strong person can extend or contract their arm."

msgctxt "mn152:8.10"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena "
"uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, "
"upekkhā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr ""
"Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, "
"and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and "
"equanimity becomes stabilized."

msgctxt "mn152:8.11"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā kāyaviññeyyesu "
"phoṭṭhabbesu."
msgstr ""
"In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of "
"the faculties regarding touches known by the body."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn152:9.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati manāpaṃ, "
"uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when a mendicant knows a thought with their mind, liking, "
"disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them."

msgctxt "mn152:9.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

msgctxt "mn152:9.3"
msgid ""
